In a press conference, President Biden condemned Russia's recent actions in Ukraine, stating that Russia has declared two regions of Ukraine as independent states and is now setting up a rationale to take more territory by force. He announced the imposition of sanctions on Russia, including blocking sanctions on two Russian financial institutions and comprehensive sanctions on Russian sovereign debt. The United States will also impose sanctions on Russia's elites and their family members. Additionally, Biden stated that the Nord Stream 2 pipeline will not move forward. The United States will continue to provide defensive assistance to Ukraine and reinforce its NATO allies. Biden expressed concern that Russia is planning a massive military attack on Ukraine and urged Russia to pursue diplomacy. He emphasized that the United States and its allies are united in their support for Ukraine and opposition to Russian aggression.